Mamelodi Sundowns footballer Gift Motupa has been involved in an accident. Daily Sun learnt that the 23-year-old footballer was on his way to Polokowane with his uncle when the accident happened on the R37 road earlier today. Shortly after the accident, paramedics rushed to the scene and the footballer and his uncle only sustained minor injuries. Details around the cause of the are still not clear, but the front part of his white VW is crashed. Motupa sporting career kicked off when he joined Baroka. He recently joined Sundowns on a five year contract, and was set to make his debut for team soon as his returning from injury. More details to come.